    <h2 style="text-align:center;">About the System</h2>
    <p>
      The UDOM Lost and Found Items Management System is an innovative digital platform designed to connect students, staff, and members of the broader University of Dodoma community. The system provides a secure and efficient way to report, track, and recover lost or found items across all UDOM campuses. Whether an item is misplaced unintentionally, left behind in a lecture hall, or retrieved from a dishonest situation such as theft, this system plays a critical role in its safe return.
    </p>

    <p>
      In a university environment as vibrant and populated as UDOM, it's common for personal belongings like ID cards, books, electronics, or bags to go missing. Sometimes, these items are found by well-meaning individuals within or around the university who don't know how or where to return them. This system serves as the bridge â€” enabling any finder, whether a student, staff member, or even a resident of Dodoma, to report the found item and ensure it reaches its rightful owner.
    </p>

    <p>
      The platform allows users to upload details such as the type of item, location found or lost, and attach images to make identification easier. Registered users receive updates and can check listings of found or missing items. The feedback mechanism also ensures users can follow up or provide additional information, which boosts transparency and user involvement.
    </p>

    <p>
      The system not only minimizes stress and inconvenience caused by losing important belongings, but also builds a culture of responsibility and collaboration. It encourages honesty and trust among the UDOM community, reduces item hoarding, and ultimately promotes safety across campuses. This effort is part of a larger goal to digitize student services and streamline communication between students, staff, and university administration regarding personal property matters.
    </p>
